         <description>"Bob Scearce was born in Cincinnati, Ohio, on June 16, 1912. He was
            raised in Bedford, Ind., but his family later moved to Gulfport, Miss., then Baton
            Rouge, La. Scearce attended Louisiana State University from 1933 to 1938 and graduated
            with majors in speech and journalism. He began writing his newspaper column, ""Set the
            Hook Hard,"" for the Baton Rouge Morning Advocate during his junior year in college. He
            worked for WJBO radio (1939-1953) and hosted a television program, ""The Great
            Outdoors"" (1953-1986)."</description>
      </name>
